Press Secretary Jay Carney gave a briefing on various topics including the President's statement on the Affordable Care Act, the administration's efforts to expand domestic energy production, the issue of patent trolls and their impact on innovation, and the nomination of three judges for the D.C. Circuit Court. Carney also addressed the situation in Syria and expressed concern about the reports of the use of chemical weapons. He emphasized the need to gather more evidence and establish the facts before making any policy decisions. Carney also discussed the protests in Turkey and called on all parties to refrain from violence. He mentioned that the President has been working to build support for immigration reform and has had numerous conversations with lawmakers. Carney acknowledged the backlog of disability claims for veterans and stated that the President has directed Secretary Shinseki to address the issue and eliminate the backlog by 2015.